# ==============================================================================

# Examples
terraform-up-and-running-code/

# 1. Terragrunt Cache (CRITICAL)
# Terragrunt creates this hidden folder to store copies of your code, 
# injected files, and provider binaries. Never commit this.
.terragrunt-cache/

# 2. Terraform Working Directory
# Local cache for providers and modules managed by the terraform binary.
.terraform/

# 3. State Files
# Even though we use S3, sometimes local state files or backups are created 
# during migrations or testing. These should remain local.
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*

# 4. Crash Logs & Debugging
# In case of execution errors, these files might contain sensitive environment info.
*.log
.terragrunt-debug-*
crash.log

# 5. Dependency Lock File
# Optional: Some teams commit this for consistency, but during learning, 
# it's often ignored to avoid OS-specific conflicts (Linux vs Windows/Mac).
.terraform.lock.hcl

# 6. Generated Files
# Since we use the 'generate' block in Terragrunt, these files are 
# ephemeral and should not be tracked by Git.
backend.tf
provider.tf

# 7. Sensitive Variables (Secrets)
# Files containing private keys, passwords, or personal AWS credentials.
*.tfvars
*.tfvars.json
.env